                    <msContents>
                        <summary> This work by Inaba Katsu, published in 1801, contains illustrations showing patients with various internal ailments, and in each the location of the pain or discomfort is indicated with printed patches of green. Each condition is discussed in katakana-majiri script and prescriptions for treatment are provided. Incomplete; only volume 2.</summary>

                        <textLang mainLang="ja" source="IANA">Japanese</textLang>

